WEBVTT

02:04.708 --> 02:05.708
Charles...

02:05.958 --> 02:07.073
Isn't this great?

02:07.333 --> 02:08.333
Yeah.

02:12.500 --> 02:13.831
Good afternoon.

02:19.583 --> 02:21.744
What wouldn't I do
to get my hands on her.

02:22.000 --> 02:23.786
Get your hands on who?

02:24.250 --> 02:27.208
"The challenger." $20-million airplane.

02:27.667 --> 02:29.147
What'd you think I was talking about?

02:29.333 --> 02:31.324
- Come on, Charles.
- Charles, you coming?

02:31.583 --> 02:33.949
Mr. morse, your assistant
asked me to give you this.

02:34.208 --> 02:35.288
Charles morse?

02:35.750 --> 02:38.457
The billionaire?
My god, is that who you are?

02:39.833 --> 02:40.868
Yeah.

02:44.625 --> 02:46.206
I've taken the Liberty, sir...

02:46.458 --> 02:48.178
Of talking to the pilot
of the amphibian.

02:48.417 --> 02:53.161
I've checked the engine log.
Plane seems to be in good shape.

02:53.417 --> 02:57.330
I would not advise you to fly under
any low ceiling, bird strike, or ice.

02:57.583 --> 03:00.325
- What's bird strike?
- Flocks of birds. Hit, we're dead.

03:00.583 --> 03:02.744
Yes, especially this time of year.

03:03.000 --> 03:05.662
Any questions,
I'll fly you in and out myself.

03:05.917 --> 03:08.989
- We'll be fine.
- I told you you'd have a good time.

03:09.250 --> 03:11.161
- When will you require a plane back?
- Bob?

03:11.417 --> 03:14.830
They want the film in New York,
36 hours. I'd say 8 tomorrow night.

03:15.250 --> 03:16.250
8:00 tomorrow night.

03:16.500 --> 03:18.365
- Yes, sir.
- Thank you.

03:50.750 --> 03:52.115
Can't handle northern weather?

03:52.417 --> 03:53.577
I'll be all right.

03:56.083 --> 03:57.619
Is that a new watch?

03:58.583 --> 04:01.655
Yeah. Dual time zone.
Tells the time in two places.

04:02.167 --> 04:03.373
What for?

04:03.833 --> 04:08.247
If I'm in L.A. and want the time
in New York, I don't have to add 3.

06:00.917 --> 06:03.533
You built this place by yourself.

06:03.792 --> 06:06.659
Yes, ma'am.
Been building it all my life.

06:11.083 --> 06:13.825
Okay, right this way, folks.

06:14.958 --> 06:18.576
You don't have to worry about keys,
because we got no locks.

06:18.833 --> 06:22.121
Kitchen is always open.
You can fix whatever you like.

06:22.375 --> 06:25.617
The bedrooms and outhouses
are upstairs.

06:25.875 --> 06:27.957
We want you to relax,
kick off your shoes...

06:28.208 --> 06:31.120
And just get down-home comfortable.

06:32.083 --> 06:33.448
Hey, Stephen.

06:34.167 --> 06:35.407
This is what I'm talking about.

06:35.708 --> 06:38.370
See? That's what I want for tomorrow.

06:39.167 --> 06:40.407
An unsentimental photograph.

06:40.667 --> 06:42.953
To get a truly
unselfconscious photograph...

06:43.208 --> 06:45.745
You have to go back
to the 19th century.

06:46.000 --> 06:47.206
How old is that?

06:47.458 --> 06:48.789
Took it last fall.

06:49.292 --> 06:51.658
That's Jack hawk. A friend of mine.

06:52.750 --> 06:53.910
You took the photo?

06:54.167 --> 06:57.534
I took the photo. He took the bear.

06:57.792 --> 07:00.158
I'd be hunting with him now,
you weren't here...

07:01.042 --> 07:03.158
And I had my rifle sighted in.

07:03.417 --> 07:05.157
You interested in books?

07:06.292 --> 07:07.953
Yeah. Why can't you?

07:08.208 --> 07:09.448
What?

07:09.750 --> 07:12.207
Why can't you get your rifle
sighted in?

07:12.458 --> 07:14.540
I need to rig up a bench rest.

07:15.292 --> 07:17.453
An ironing board
makes a good bench rest.

07:17.708 --> 07:19.699
No disrespect...

07:20.500 --> 07:22.786
I'm surprised you know
what a bench rest is.

07:23.042 --> 07:26.910
Charles knows what everything is.
Got a question, ask him.

07:27.500 --> 07:30.458
Take a mighty accomplished man
to claim that.

07:30.750 --> 07:32.490
I don't claim anything.

07:32.750 --> 07:34.160
Ask him. See if I'm wrong.

07:34.583 --> 07:36.073
Bet you can't stump him.

07:36.333 --> 07:37.698
Bet you I can.

07:40.167 --> 07:41.907
I'll tell you what...

07:43.083 --> 07:45.870
I will give you $5...

07:46.333 --> 07:49.780
You can tell me what's on
the other side of this blade.

07:53.417 --> 07:55.282
It's a rabbit smoking a pipe.

07:59.167 --> 08:01.203
A rabbit smoking a pipe.

08:01.458 --> 08:04.370
Why in the world would
that be, Charles?

08:06.167 --> 08:10.615
It's a symbol of the cree Indians.
On one side, there's a panther...

08:10.875 --> 08:13.366
On the other, his prey, the rabbit.

08:13.625 --> 08:15.081
He sits...

08:15.333 --> 08:16.333
Unafraid.

08:16.583 --> 08:17.868
He smokes his pipe.

08:18.583 --> 08:20.323
It's a traditional motif.

08:20.958 --> 08:22.994
Why is he unafraid?

08:24.125 --> 08:26.241
Because he's smarter than the panther.

08:27.292 --> 08:28.327
Sir...

08:29.542 --> 08:31.328
You impress me.

08:33.000 --> 08:34.000
Thank you.

08:34.167 --> 08:35.657
Amazing accomplishment.

08:36.167 --> 08:38.828
No, it's not an accomplishment.

08:39.125 --> 08:40.740
- It's a freak.
- Is that so?

08:42.417 --> 08:43.417
Yeah.

08:45.042 --> 08:46.828
I seem to retain all these facts...

08:47.083 --> 08:50.155
But putting them to any useful
purpose is another matter.

08:53.083 --> 08:54.914
Hey, listen up, folks.

08:55.167 --> 08:57.749
We got a problem with bears
around here.

08:58.000 --> 09:02.539
Now, never leave food uncovered,
even in the lodge.

09:02.792 --> 09:03.827
Never!

09:04.083 --> 09:06.165
You see a bear near you...

09:06.417 --> 09:08.328
Stand still.

09:09.250 --> 09:13.448
Let him know that you know
that he sees you.

09:14.917 --> 09:16.873
Then back up...

09:17.708 --> 09:19.949
Real slow.

09:21.458 --> 09:23.198
Anybody's in trouble...

09:23.458 --> 09:25.164
Get my attention.

09:25.417 --> 09:27.908
I'll be on it like a duck
on a June bug.

09:28.167 --> 09:30.453
Now make yourselves comfortable.

09:30.708 --> 09:32.824
On that note, I'm going to bed.

09:34.208 --> 09:35.698
Shut up.

09:57.333 --> 09:59.449
Lord, I'm bushed.

10:00.375 --> 10:01.455
New book?

10:02.500 --> 10:04.832
It's about surviving
in the wilderness.

10:05.083 --> 10:07.165
You're always reading something.

10:07.542 --> 10:10.124
My secretary gave it to me.
Do you know why?

10:12.833 --> 10:14.573
Do you know why she gave me the book?

10:14.875 --> 10:17.036
That guy gave me the creeps,
with all that...

10:18.000 --> 10:19.786
Lwlalk about the bear.

10:21.500 --> 10:23.036
Why she gave you the book?

10:23.417 --> 10:24.953
You're the salt of the earth.

10:25.208 --> 10:26.414
Is that so?

10:27.042 --> 10:28.873
You're a most excellent man.

10:29.167 --> 10:30.782
That's why I married you.

10:32.375 --> 10:34.616
You're the only woman
I've ever wanted.

10:36.167 --> 10:38.499
Then see what a lucky guy you are?

10:38.750 --> 10:39.865
Yes, I do.

10:49.333 --> 10:51.995
This is a special day for me.
You know that?

10:52.583 --> 10:53.698
I know it is.

10:54.500 --> 10:57.037
I'm really glad you came away with us.

10:57.458 --> 10:59.244
You got to get away more often.

11:07.292 --> 11:09.408
Can you go and get me a sandwich?

11:11.167 --> 11:12.373
Of course.

11:15.042 --> 11:16.873
Did I ever tell you you're an angel?

11:17.125 --> 11:18.125
No.

11:18.833 --> 11:20.789
Everything but the wings.

11:23.542 --> 11:24.952
The sandwich.

13:42.000 --> 13:43.035
Surprise!

13:48.042 --> 13:51.079
Oh, my god.
Charles, are you all right?

13:51.333 --> 13:53.699
Charles, are you all right?

13:54.375 --> 13:55.865
Jesus! I'm sorry!

13:56.833 --> 13:58.619
I'm so sorry.

13:59.750 --> 14:00.910
Are you all right?

14:01.250 --> 14:02.456
I'm fine.

14:03.750 --> 14:04.990
Are you sure?

14:09.583 --> 14:12.370
- Happy birthday.
- So you didn't forget.

14:13.250 --> 14:14.706
I could never forget you.

14:17.208 --> 14:18.789
I could never forget.

14:23.958 --> 14:25.243
Champagne for Charles.

14:28.417 --> 14:30.203
Blow out the candle, Charles.

14:34.292 --> 14:36.499
May I have your attention, please?

14:36.750 --> 14:39.708
Can I get serious for a moment?
Charles...

14:40.417 --> 14:41.782
Thank you for your...

14:42.417 --> 14:43.657
Good nature...

14:43.917 --> 14:45.123
Your intelligence...

14:46.000 --> 14:47.581
Your generosity...

14:48.833 --> 14:51.950
Forgive us for this charade.

14:52.500 --> 14:54.707
And, in short, happy birthday.

14:54.958 --> 14:56.289
- Happy birthday.
- Thank you.

14:57.958 --> 15:00.199
To a good companion and a good sport.

15:00.667 --> 15:02.203
And a very brave man.

15:02.458 --> 15:03.458
Hear, hear.

15:03.500 --> 15:04.500
Here.

15:04.750 --> 15:05.750
Thank you.

15:13.750 --> 15:15.661
Mickey, that's beautiful!

15:16.250 --> 15:17.956
There's an engraving inside.

15:18.875 --> 15:20.035
What's it say?

15:21.083 --> 15:23.369
It says, " to my beloved husband...

15:24.333 --> 15:25.618
On his birthday...

15:27.167 --> 15:28.807
From the luckiest woman
in the world."

15:29.417 --> 15:31.328
This is a superb present. Thanks.

15:31.583 --> 15:33.824
May you wear it in good health.

15:35.833 --> 15:37.118
Here you go.

15:38.042 --> 15:39.782
Here you go, birthday boy.

15:41.833 --> 15:42.833
Thank you.

15:52.250 --> 15:53.250
What is it?

15:54.292 --> 15:57.784
- Look at that! Nice, I like that.
- It's beautiful.

15:58.292 --> 16:00.829
You got to give the donor a coin.

16:01.250 --> 16:02.615
Old superstition.

16:03.167 --> 16:04.782
Yes. Thank you. Here.

16:05.042 --> 16:06.373
Give him a coin?

16:06.875 --> 16:10.322
If someone gives you a knife you
should give him a coin in return...

16:10.583 --> 16:12.164
Or it cuts the friendship.

16:13.042 --> 16:14.248
Thank you, Bob.

16:16.833 --> 16:18.118
Getting late. Work day tomorrow.

16:18.375 --> 16:20.331
- Let's pack it in.
- Yeah, to bed!

16:20.583 --> 16:21.583
Happy birthday.

16:21.667 --> 16:22.667
Happy birthday.

16:23.208 --> 16:24.618
Thanks. Thank you.

16:24.875 --> 16:25.875
Good night.

16:26.458 --> 16:28.915
- Happy birthday, Charles.
- Sleep well.

16:29.167 --> 16:31.123
- Happy birthday to you.
- Thank you.

16:34.250 --> 16:35.990
Nice looking lady.

16:36.667 --> 16:38.032
Your wife?

16:39.417 --> 16:40.417
Yes.

16:41.250 --> 16:42.410
Why do you ask?

16:46.375 --> 16:48.286
Just like to know who everybody is.

16:53.000 --> 16:54.115
Hold on, it's flaring.

16:54.375 --> 16:55.490
Got itl

16:55.750 --> 16:57.456
and, let's go.

16:59.833 --> 17:01.869
Redlly beautiful. Great!

17:03.208 --> 17:04.823
That's great!

17:06.041 --> 17:07.623
- Could you lift that up?
- My god.

17:08.041 --> 17:09.373
Give me the 180.

17:09.833 --> 17:11.164
Excuse me.

17:13.833 --> 17:15.789
Okay, great. One more, let's go.

17:16.916 --> 17:18.531
We'll do one more roll. One more.

17:19.541 --> 17:20.577
Officer.

17:21.083 --> 17:23.665
Can I sunbathe on this beach nude?

17:23.916 --> 17:25.498
Sorry, it's against the rules.

17:25.750 --> 17:27.240
But I have a divine right.

17:27.500 --> 17:28.785
Your left ain't bad either.

17:29.875 --> 17:31.490
Let's go. Check it, please.

17:40.417 --> 17:41.953
Kodiak bear.

17:42.458 --> 17:44.665
He'll kill you as he'll look at you.

17:48.792 --> 17:53.206
And the ones that killed a man,
manhunter for the rest of his life.

17:53.458 --> 17:56.495
Nothing he'd rather eat.
Got the taste of human flesh.

17:56.750 --> 17:58.786
A man-killing machine.

17:59.542 --> 18:01.828
Let's get the boy's shoes polished.

18:02.083 --> 18:05.746
- Do I need to walk you through this?
- It's just the shoes.

18:06.000 --> 18:08.332
Scrap the shoes for god's sake.

18:08.583 --> 18:12.201
What is this? Brain surgery?
It's a fucking pair of shoes!

18:12.458 --> 18:15.120
- Let's get James down here.
- Robert, he's sick.

18:17.042 --> 18:20.034
He's sick, the shoes look like shit
and things I ask...

18:20.292 --> 18:22.408
This is really fucking lame.

18:22.667 --> 18:25.283
The inside of a banana peel
will shine shoes.

18:29.542 --> 18:30.542
Come with me.

18:30.750 --> 18:34.197
A fount of information. A banana.
You should know that!

18:37.708 --> 18:39.949
He's sick, Bob. James is sick.

18:40.500 --> 18:42.240
How sick is he?

18:42.500 --> 18:44.536
He'd have to get better to die.

18:51.208 --> 18:52.208
That guy!

18:53.458 --> 18:55.824
That guy.
He's the guy for my photograph.

18:57.250 --> 18:58.865
Excuse me, where is this guy?

18:59.125 --> 19:01.286
He's your friend, right? Where is he?

19:01.542 --> 19:04.909
This is the guy we want.
Not some fucking model.

19:05.167 --> 19:06.167
Where is he?

19:06.333 --> 19:09.200
Jack hawk? Cabin up north. 80 miles.

19:09.667 --> 19:11.498
Does he have a phone?

19:11.750 --> 19:15.447
No phone. No radio.
Any case, he'll likely be out hunting

19:16.292 --> 19:19.250
then we'll just go and find him.
That's what we'll do.

19:24.458 --> 19:26.824
You can make a compass
out of a needle.

19:27.083 --> 19:28.198
God.

19:28.458 --> 19:30.949
That's da new one on me.

19:33.208 --> 19:35.039
Do you spend much time in the woods?

19:35.958 --> 19:38.950
No. I'm afraid most
of my knowledge is theoretical.

19:40.708 --> 19:42.164
Such a...

19:42.625 --> 19:44.161
Perfect spot.

19:45.042 --> 19:47.078
Such a privilege.

19:47.875 --> 19:49.615
It's a shame...

19:49.958 --> 19:52.165
Everyone can't enjoy it.

19:54.708 --> 19:56.073
It is remote and...

19:56.333 --> 19:57.333
True.

19:57.458 --> 20:01.371
You think this spot is so remote
that only the few can enjoy it.

20:01.625 --> 20:03.161
But I got a plan.

20:03.417 --> 20:08.081
I got a scheme to develop this lake
and I think you could appreciate it.

20:08.333 --> 20:10.949
No need for you
to look at these things.

20:11.208 --> 20:13.950
You can envision this
better than these folks can draw.

20:14.667 --> 20:17.249
But I want you to look
at these things.

20:17.500 --> 20:20.242
Now here's the interesting part.

20:20.500 --> 20:25.164
For only 30 or 40 million dollars
you can...

20:27.417 --> 20:28.577
I beg your pardon?

20:30.917 --> 20:34.080
I thought for a moment
you were just being courteous.

20:36.375 --> 20:37.581
What do you mean?

20:38.042 --> 20:39.998
Nothing. It's fine.

20:41.417 --> 20:44.454
- Just leave it fo me.
- Let's get him. We lose the light...

20:44.708 --> 20:46.073
We lose the light at 4:18.

20:46.333 --> 20:50.997
This is the guy we should've shot all
along. He has character in his face.

20:54.708 --> 20:55.708
What's the matter?

20:55.958 --> 20:56.958
What?

20:58.042 --> 20:59.452
It's nothing.

21:00.125 --> 21:01.990
He's jaded, that's what it is.

21:02.917 --> 21:04.123
That's it. I'm jaded.

21:04.375 --> 21:07.538
We're going on an impromptu adventure.
You come too.

21:07.792 --> 21:09.282
Charles on an adventure?

21:09.542 --> 21:13.114
That's right. What do you say,
Charles? We'll be back in 2 hours.

21:13.625 --> 21:15.832
Go. Get some air under your wings.

21:29.042 --> 21:30.248
Yeah. Okay.

21:31.708 --> 21:33.494
Behold the mighty hunter. Come on.

22:48.208 --> 22:49.948
Hello!

23:01.875 --> 23:03.615
That's just great.

23:07.792 --> 23:10.078
My model's gone bear hunting.

23:10.833 --> 23:11.833
How butch of him.

23:12.042 --> 23:13.248
Where's he going?

23:13.542 --> 23:14.542
Big bass lake?

23:15.458 --> 23:17.870
It's about 20 miles northwest!

23:18.250 --> 23:21.037
And we're left here taking
a picture of sweet Fanny Anne.

23:21.292 --> 23:22.327
What do you say?

23:22.583 --> 23:23.583
Whai?!

23:28.875 --> 23:30.411
- Should we chance it?
- Be careful.

23:30.667 --> 23:31.702
Careful of what?

23:31.958 --> 23:33.118
It's a deadfall.

23:33.583 --> 23:34.583
What's a deadfall?

23:34.750 --> 23:37.207
- I's a pit to catch bears.
- What're we being careful of?

23:37.792 --> 23:40.955
It's a pit. They cover it up.
Should we press on?

23:41.208 --> 23:43.915
- Should we be bold?
- You really need to find this guy?

23:44.167 --> 23:46.624
I need to get that film.
A good plan today is...

23:46.875 --> 23:49.708
Better than a perfect plan tomorrow.
What do you say?

23:49.958 --> 23:51.539
Okay, let's be bold.

23:52.125 --> 23:54.832
There's the spirit
that beat the Japanese.

24:14.458 --> 24:17.370
Weather coming in from the north.
Snow, maybe.

24:25.208 --> 24:26.948
Can I tell you something?

24:27.792 --> 24:29.032
If you like.

24:30.458 --> 24:32.198
I admire the way you took that joke.

24:33.125 --> 24:34.490
Handled well.

24:35.000 --> 24:37.082
Embarrassing. You handled it well.

24:37.333 --> 24:38.333
Thank you.

24:40.250 --> 24:42.081
Tough row to hoe
if you think about it.

24:42.333 --> 24:43.618
What would that be?

24:44.625 --> 24:45.831
All that money.

24:47.375 --> 24:49.536
All the responsibility.

24:49.958 --> 24:52.995
Never knowing who your friends are.
Never knowing...

24:53.458 --> 24:55.949
What people value you for.

24:57.917 --> 24:59.157
It must be tough.

25:02.458 --> 25:04.870
Never feel sorry for a man
who owns a plane.

25:08.792 --> 25:10.657
What do you value me for, Bob?

25:13.583 --> 25:15.995
I'll tell you what,
I like your style...

25:17.000 --> 25:19.241
And I think your wife's cute too.

25:19.625 --> 25:20.865
Yes.

25:21.792 --> 25:22.872
So...

25:23.792 --> 25:25.578
How are you planning to kill me?

25:28.625 --> 25:29.625
Fuck! Hold on!

25:35.667 --> 25:36.667
What's happening?

26:04.042 --> 26:05.623
Goddamn if!

28:12.750 --> 28:13.750
Get him up.

28:13.958 --> 28:16.495
Get him up. Let's get him up.
Come on.

28:19.000 --> 28:20.000
I got him.

28:32.750 --> 28:34.160
Oh, god.

28:42.625 --> 28:44.331
Anyone got any matches?

28:45.708 --> 28:47.039
Any matches?

28:47.417 --> 28:48.623
Help me up.

28:58.292 --> 28:59.623
Oh, my god.

29:13.250 --> 29:15.616
We'll make a fire. Right here.

29:15.875 --> 29:16.990
Make a fire.

29:30.000 --> 29:31.000
That's better.

29:32.375 --> 29:33.375
Come on.

29:34.167 --> 29:35.577
Oh, god.

29:38.792 --> 29:39.907
Come on.

29:44.708 --> 29:45.708
That's it.

29:46.042 --> 29:47.623
Oh, god, no.

29:48.667 --> 29:49.667
Damn.

29:50.958 --> 29:51.958
I'm cold.

29:52.208 --> 29:55.655
Let's stop fucking about, shall we,
and get the guy warm.

29:55.917 --> 29:58.124
Hey, come on. We need those.

29:58.458 --> 29:59.664
We need them.

30:04.875 --> 30:07.992
Come, Stephen, be near the fire.
Come on, come here.

30:32.125 --> 30:34.116
I'm afraid I let the fire burn out.

30:34.375 --> 30:36.081
We only got a few flares left.

30:36.750 --> 30:38.832
Shouldn't we keep them for signaling?

30:41.375 --> 30:42.410
What we need is...

30:44.167 --> 30:47.284
What we want is wood, stacked.
For a signal fire.

30:47.542 --> 30:49.658
So when they come they'll
see the smoke.

30:52.875 --> 30:54.581
Why would they come for us?

30:56.125 --> 30:58.457
